{
  "date": "2026-03-26",
  "title": "Built to Build Each Other",
  "scriptures": [
    {
      "ref": "Isaiah 58:10-11",
      "text": "If you pour yourself out for the hungry.… then shall your light rise in the darkness.… and you shall be like a watered garden."
    },
    {
      "ref": "Ephesians 4:11-12",
      "text": "….to equip the saints for the work of ministry, for building up the body of Christ."
    }
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "key": "read_this_out_loud",
      "label": "Read This Out Loud",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You were never meant to grow alone."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You were designed to give.... and to receive."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not just to help people."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But to be helped."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not just to pour out."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But to be filled again."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Strength doesn’t live in isolation."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It flows through connection."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_devotional",
      "label": "The Devotional",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "We often think strength looks like independence."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Handle your own problems."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Carry your own weight."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Don’t need anyone."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But that’s not how the Kingdom works."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "In the Kingdom…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "strength circulates."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Isaiah says when you pour yourself out,"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "God fills you."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not before."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not instead of."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Through it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And Ephesians shows us something even deeper:"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "God designed people with different gifts,"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "not so one person has everything…"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "….but so everyone needs someone."
        },
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "Strengthen someone",
            "Equip someone",
            "Lift someone",
            "Build someone"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And at the same time…."
        },
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "Encouragement",
            "Correction",
            "Support",
            "Truth"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This is not weakness."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This is design."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_shift",
      "label": "The Shift",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Most men drift into one of two traps:"
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "👉 The Isolator - \"I don’t need anyone.”",
            "👉 The Consumer - \"I just need people to help me.”"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But the Kingdom calls you into something better:"
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "👉 The Contributor"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not just taking."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not just giving."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But living in the flow of both."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because when you only receive, you stagnate."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And when you only give, you burn out."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But when you do both…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You come alive."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "jesus_set_the_pattern",
      "label": "Jesus Set the Pattern",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Jesus poured out constantly."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Healing. Teaching. Serving."
        },
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "Withdrew to be filled (Luke 5:16)",
            "Walked closely with a few (the 12, the 3)",
            "Received support (Luke 8:3)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Even Jesus didn’t operate in isolation."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "So why do we?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_truth",
      "label": "The Truth",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "If you only live for yourself, you shrink."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "If you only serve without connection, you drain."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But when you step into God’s design…."
        },
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "A source to others",
            "And a vessel God keeps refilling"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "A watered garden."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not a dry well."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You were never meant to just survive."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You were meant to strengthen the body and be strengthened by it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "reflection",
      "label": "Reflection",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "Where have I been trying to do life alone?",
            "Where am I receiving, but not giving?",
            "Who around me needs what God has already placed in me?",
            "Who do I need to stop avoiding and start opening up to?"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "declaration",
      "label": "Declaration",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "I am not isolated.",
            "I am not self-sufficient.",
            "I am part of something bigger.",
            "I give.",
            "I receive.",
            "I build and I am built.",
            "God flows through me, not just to me."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "action_step",
      "label": "Action Step",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Today, step into the flow."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "👉 Give something:",
            "Encouragement, truth, time, presence.",
            "👉 Receive something:",
            "Ask for help. Open up. Let someone in.",
            "👉 Strengthen one person intentionally."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Don’t overcomplicate it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Just move."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "one_sentence_to_carry",
      "label": "One Sentence to Carry",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "text": "“I’m not meant to do life alone, I’m built to build others.” - TheWrkShop"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "__insert_block_header": "2026-03-26_isaiah-58-10-11_built-to-build-each-other|"
}
